m_szDocSumamry: Coonooer Bridge Begins Generating Cheapest Wind Energy In Australia March 3rd, 2016 by Guest Contributor   Originally published on RenewEconomy . by Sophie Vorrath Victoria’s Coonooer Bridge wind farm has begun producing what is assumed to be the cheapest wind energy in Australia, after the project became the first from the ACT government’s hugely successful wind auction to generate power.
